<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">How Our Pricing Works</p>
    <h2>We quote labor and parts separately. Here&rsquo;s why that matters to you.</h2>
    <div class="body-text">
      <p>Many appliance repair companies in Los Angeles use flat-rate BlueBook pricing &mdash; a single bundled number that covers labor and parts together before the technician has even opened the unit. It sounds simple. But it means you have no idea how much is labor, how much is the part, or whether either number is fair for your specific repair.</p>
      <p>We quote differently. The $89 diagnostic fee covers the service call and the full diagnosis. Once we know exactly what failed, we give you two numbers: labor and the specific OEM part needed. You see the full breakdown before we start. You can look up the part cost. You know what you&rsquo;re paying for.</p>
      <p>A flat-rate quote before diagnosis is either padded with margin for uncertainty, or it doesn&rsquo;t change regardless of how simple the job turns out to be. Our model means you pay for what the repair actually requires. Most of our repairs come in at the lower end of the labor ranges on this page.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="transparency-block">
      <div class="tr-card them">
        <h3>Flat-Rate BlueBook pricing</h3>
        <ul class="tr-list">
          <li>Single price before diagnosis</li>
          <li>Labor and parts bundled &mdash; no breakdown</li>
          <li>You don&rsquo;t know what the part costs</li>
          <li>Price padded to cover uncertainty on every job</li>
          <li>Doesn&rsquo;t adjust based on actual complexity</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="tr-card us">
        <h3>Our approach &mdash; labor + parts separate</h3>
        <ul class="tr-list">
          <li>Diagnose first, then quote</li>
          <li>Labor and parts shown as separate line items</li>
          <li>You see exactly what the OEM part costs</li>
          <li>Price reflects the actual repair needed</li>
          <li>$89 diagnostic applied to the total</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

