<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Cost Factors</p>
    <h2>What affects refrigerator repair cost in Los Angeles</h2>
    <div class="factors-grid">
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128295;</div><h3>Type of failure</h3><p>A door gasket is a straightforward swap. A compressor replacement involves refrigerant evacuation, new component installation, and system recharge &mdash; more time, more complexity, higher labor.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#127991;</div><h3>Appliance brand</h3><p>Standard brands have widely available parts at lower cost. Sub-Zero, Miele, Gaggenau use proprietary OEM-only parts at a significant premium &mdash; which is precisely why we quote them as a separate line item, not buried in a flat rate.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128197;</div><h3>Age of the unit</h3><p>Parts availability drops for units over 12&ndash;15 years old. Some older models require sourced parts with longer lead times. We tell you this upfront &mdash; before you approve the repair.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#127959;</div><h3>Built-in vs. freestanding</h3><p>Built-in refrigerators (Sub-Zero, Thermador, Miele) require more access work &mdash; removing trim panels, navigating custom cabinetry, limited clearance. This adds labor time and shows in the higher luxury labor ranges.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#127777;</div><h3>LA climate conditions</h3><p>Coastal areas (Santa Monica, Malibu) see accelerated coil corrosion from salt air. Inland Valley homes deal with dust-clogged condensers. Both add diagnostic and cleaning steps to refrigerator service calls.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#9889;</div><h3>Root cause vs. symptom</h3><p>A struggling compressor causes evaporator ice buildup &mdash; two problems with one root. We diagnose the root cause and fix it. With separate labor and parts quotes, you see exactly what each fix costs.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Repair vs. Replace</p>
    <h2>When to repair, when to replace</h2>
    <p class="lead">We give you an honest assessment after diagnosis &mdash; the same one we&rsquo;d give if it were our own refrigerator.</p>
    <div class="rvr-grid">
      <div class="rvr-card repair">
        <h3>Repair makes sense when:</h3>
        <ul class="rvr-list">
          <li>Unit is under 10 years old</li>
          <li>Total repair (labor + parts) is under 50% of replacement value</li>
          <li>It&rsquo;s a built-in unit &mdash; replacement means kitchen renovation</li>
          <li>Luxury brand (Sub-Zero, Miele) &mdash; these last 20+ years with good repair</li>
          <li>Single component failure, not systemic breakdown</li>
          <li>Refrigerant system is intact</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="rvr-card replace">
        <h3>Replace makes more sense when:</h3>
        <ul class="rvr-list">
          <li>Standard brand unit is 12&ndash;15+ years old</li>
          <li>Compressor failed on a low-end unit under 8 years old</li>
          <li>Multiple components failing in the same repair window</li>
          <li>Parts discontinued or have 4+ week lead times</li>
          <li>Total repair exceeds 60&ndash;70% of a comparable new unit</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="margin-top:32px;">
      <p class="sl">Expected Lifespan by Brand</p>
      <table class="lifespan-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Brand Category</th><th>Expected Lifespan</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="hi">Standard (Samsung, LG, GE, Whirlpool)</td><td>10&ndash;14 years</td><td>Shorter in coastal LA due to salt air</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="hi">Mid-range (KitchenAid, Bosch, Electrolux)</td><td>12&ndash;16 years</td><td>With proper maintenance</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="hi">Luxury (Sub-Zero, Wolf)</td><td>20&ndash;25+ years</td><td>If maintained and repaired promptly</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="hi">Miele / Liebherr / Gaggenau</td><td>18&ndash;22 years</td><td>European engineering standard</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

