    <p class="sl">FAQ</p>
    <h2>Questions about refrigerator repair costs in Los Angeles</h2>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How much does refrigerator repair cost in Los Angeles?</div><div class="faq-a">Labor typically runs $200&ndash;$440 for standard brands. Parts are quoted separately after diagnosis. The $89 diagnostic fee applies to the repair total when you approve the work. Sub-Zero and luxury brands run $320&ndash;$910+ in labor.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Why do you quote labor and parts separately instead of a flat rate?</div><div class="faq-a">Many LA repair companies use flat-rate BlueBook pricing that bundles labor and parts into a single number before diagnosis. We quote them separately so you see exactly what you&rsquo;re paying for. A flat rate before diagnosis is either padded for uncertainty or doesn&rsquo;t reflect the actual complexity of your specific repair.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Are parts included in the quoted labor price?</div><div class="faq-a">No &mdash; the prices on this page are labor only. After diagnosis we identify the exact part needed and quote it as a separate line item. You see both numbers before approving anything. OEM parts used wherever available.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How much does Sub-Zero refrigerator repair cost in Los Angeles?</div><div class="faq-a">Labor for Sub-Zero repair runs $320&ndash;$910+ depending on the failure. Sub-Zero uses proprietary components and sealed systems. OEM parts are priced at a premium and quoted separately after diagnosis.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Is refrigerator repair worth it vs. buying new?</div><div class="faq-a">For units under 10 years old, repair almost always makes economic sense. For luxury built-ins like Sub-Zero, repair nearly always wins &mdash; replacing a built-in means a kitchen renovation. We give you an honest assessment after diagnosis.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What is the $89 diagnostic fee?</div><div class="faq-a">We charge $89 to come out and diagnose the problem. That fee applies to the repair total when you approve the work &mdash; effectively free when we fix it. If you decide not to repair, you pay $89 and we leave. No pressure.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What warranty do you provide on refrigerator repair?</div><div class="faq-a">90 days on parts and labor. Same issue within 90 days &mdash; we come back at no charge. OEM parts wherever available.</div></div>
    </div>
